{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 15:28:18.154899", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- Faulty device(s) localized: 20.0.0.100 (SDN Controller)\n- Root cause selected: sdn_controller_crash\n\nNotes:\n- Diagnosis indicates SDN controller is not accepting OpenFlow (TCP port 6633) connections while controller IP is ICMP-reachable. Switches have no OpenFlow session and no flows; with fail_mode=secure they drop unknown traffic, causing host-to-host data-plane isolation in 10.0.0.0/24.\n- Recommended next steps (not part of submission): check controller process, listening ports (ss -ltnp), controller logs, firewall rules, and confirm OpenFlow port (6633 vs 6653).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2437, "output_tokens": 162, "total_tokens": 2599, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
